comment:
* Convenience class that contains string constants used
         * to create contact {@link android.content.Intent Intents}.

variables.name: ACTION
variables.comment: The action code to use when adding a contact

variables.name: FULL_MODE
variables.comment: * If present, forces a bypass of quick insert mode.

variables.name: NAME
variables.comment:
* The extra field for the contact name. *

Type: String

variables.name: PHONETIC_NAME
variables.comment:
* The extra field for the contact phonetic name. *

Type: String

variables.name: COMPANY
variables.comment:
* The extra field for the contact company. *

Type: String

variables.name: JOB_TITLE
variables.comment:
* The extra field for the contact job title. *

Type: String

variables.name: NOTES
variables.comment:
* The extra field for the contact notes. *

Type: String

variables.name: PHONE
variables.comment:
* The extra field for the contact phone number. *

Type: String

variables.name: PHONE_TYPE
variables.comment:
* The extra field for the contact phone number type. *

Type: Either an integer value from * {@link CommonDataKinds.Phone}, * or a string specifying a custom label.

variables.name: PHONE_ISPRIMARY
variables.comment:
* The extra field for the phone isprimary flag. *

Type: boolean

variables.name: SECONDARY_PHONE
variables.comment:
* The extra field for an optional second contact phone number. *

Type: String

variables.name: SECONDARY_PHONE_TYPE
variables.comment:
* The extra field for an optional second contact phone number type. *

Type: Either an integer value from * {@link CommonDataKinds.Phone}, * or a string specifying a custom label.

variables.name: TERTIARY_PHONE
variables.comment:
* The extra field for an optional third contact phone number. *

Type: String

variables.name: TERTIARY_PHONE_TYPE
variables.comment:
* The extra field for an optional third contact phone number type. *

Type: Either an integer value from * {@link CommonDataKinds.Phone}, * or a string specifying a custom label.

variables.name: EMAIL
variables.comment:
* The extra field for the contact email address. *

Type: String

variables.name: EMAIL_TYPE
variables.comment:
* The extra field for the contact email type. *

Type: Either an integer value from * {@link CommonDataKinds.Email} * or a string specifying a custom label.

variables.name: EMAIL_ISPRIMARY
variables.comment:
* The extra field for the email isprimary flag. *

Type: boolean

variables.name: SECONDARY_EMAIL
variables.comment:
* The extra field for an optional second contact email address. *

Type: String

variables.name: SECONDARY_EMAIL_TYPE
variables.comment:
* The extra field for an optional second contact email type. *

Type: Either an integer value from * {@link CommonDataKinds.Email} * or a string specifying a custom label.

variables.name: TERTIARY_EMAIL
variables.comment:
* The extra field for an optional third contact email address. *

Type: String

variables.name: TERTIARY_EMAIL_TYPE
variables.comment:
* The extra field for an optional third contact email type. *

Type: Either an integer value from * {@link CommonDataKinds.Email} * or a string specifying a custom label.

variables.name: POSTAL
variables.comment:
* The extra field for the contact postal address. *

Type: String

variables.name: POSTAL_TYPE
variables.comment:
* The extra field for the contact postal address type. *

Type: Either an integer value from * {@link CommonDataKinds.StructuredPostal} * or a string specifying a custom label.

variables.name: POSTAL_ISPRIMARY
variables.comment:
* The extra field for the postal isprimary flag. *

Type: boolean

variables.name: IM_HANDLE
variables.comment:
* The extra field for an IM handle. *

Type: String

variables.name: IM_PROTOCOL
variables.comment: * The extra field for the IM protocol

variables.name: IM_ISPRIMARY
variables.comment:
* The extra field for the IM isprimary flag. *

Type: boolean

variables.name: DATA
EXTRA_ACCOUNT
variables.comment:
* Used to specify the account in which to create the new contact. *

* If this value is not provided, the user is presented with a disambiguation * dialog to chose an account *

* Type: {@link Account}

variables.name: EXTRA_DATA_SET
variables.comment:
* Used to specify the data set within the account in which to create the * new contact. *

* This value is optional - if it is not specified, the contact will be * created in the base account, with no data set. *

* Type: String
